Understanding of theory and practice of document and records management in cretion and implementation of systems. Methods and techniques on functions and processes analysis, creation of process schemes. Compiling principle instruments necessary for creating, implementing and use of records management system i.e classification scheme. Functional requirements of document / records management system is covered. Use of metadata in the systems. Project management in development and implementation of document and records management system.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To give in-depth knowledge on the document and records management. To get practical skills for creation of basic documents for record system and development and implementation of records management system.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon the completion of the course the student: 1) can create organization's records system; 2) knows how to integrate records management system with other organization's information systems; 3) analysis organization's functions and activities (processes) from the documentation point of view; can choose propriate analysis methods; 4) compile principal instruments form records management i.e. business classification scheme; 5) knows how to integrate records management processes with organization's core and supporting proccesses; 6) knows functionalities of the document and records management systems and their implementation; 7) can choose metadata.
